<div id="review_116505526" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/116505526" />
    <a title="alysa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2524591-alysa"><img alt="alysa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1276835101p2/2524591.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/116505526?book_show_action=true">Aug 12, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="alysa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="alysa" href="/user/show/2524591-alysa">alysa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780385665308" href="/book/show/4078927-little-bee">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer116505526" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7403857283237565745">UGH, What can I say. I hated this book! If you want to read about the most depressing events of a human life than this one is for you. What an emotional downer this book is. It does nothing but show you the evil that can be present in human nature from extramarital affairs all the way to murder. The overall gist of the story is about a Nigerian refugee. Yes, it is a story that should be told, but I would rather read about just the facts in a news article than something I am reading for &quot;pleasure</span>
  <span id="freeText7403857283237565745" style="display:none">UGH, What can I say. I hated this book! If you want to read about the most depressing events of a human life than this one is for you. What an emotional downer this book is. It does nothing but show you the evil that can be present in human nature from extramarital affairs all the way to murder. The overall gist of the story is about a Nigerian refugee. Yes, it is a story that should be told, but I would rather read about just the facts in a news article than something I am reading for "pleasure." When I read I don't need to be depressed about the future of our world and the deprivation of human nature. So why did I read it? For my book club and I should have put it down. I only kept on because I thought there might be a silver lining or happy ending somewhere. Really, do not read this book unless you want to be totally depressed. There is not one shred of happiness in this book. And please, what mother in her right mind would take her 4 year old son to war torn Nigeria and bribe the military so she could go galavanting through the country with a criminal. Clearly it was not written by a women, to say nothing of a mother. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7403857283237565745" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


